attributionInfo.agentName: Monica Breckenridge ABR CDPE CLHMS GRI MRP PSA RSPS SFR SRES

data.description: This large home in a beautiful, sought after neighborhood is ready for its new owner. It also offers a great opportunity to build some sweat equity. The bones are good, but it needs some cosmetic help. Priced for the work that needs to be done, you can move in and increase the value in a very short time. The home backs to former appletree golf course and offers wide open views. The home itself sits on nearly a third of an acre so offers plenty of room to do almost anything you want. As you enter the dining room will be to your immediate right and is big enough to hold a large table and your china hutch. In front of you and to your left are the living room and kitchen that feature an open floor plan and vaulted ceilings. The kitchen and entry have 2" oak floors that are beautiful. The large living room will fit even the largest sectional. The main level presents three bedrooms. The master has an attached 5 piece bathroom and walk in closet. Bedrooms two and three share a full hall bath. The laundry room rounds out the main level with lots of cabinets and a sink. The basement has a huge family room with a fireplace and  a former second kitchen. Two more bedrooms another full bath and plenty of storage.  There is a walk out from the family room making this a great space for multi generational  or roommate living.
